write the unix command to count the number of words in the first 3 lines of a file.
the file will be given as a command line argument when the script contaiing your command will run.
for example, if youif the input file containing the following lines

unixis a command based operating system.
we will learn unix in this module.
this is a test file.
we are using this file to practise some commands.
we have reached the end of the file.

the output will be,
19


Solution: 
head -3|wc -w
